<paragraph blockId="15.[140,1108,729,1672]" lastBlockId="16.[140,1108,167,1109]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">
<taxonomicName box="[185,388,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingenua">
<emphasis box="[185,388,1399,1425]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Charadra ingenua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– Type locality: [
<collectingCountry box="[602,665,1398,1425]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">USA</collectingCountry>
:] Durango, 
<collectingRegion box="[810,920,1399,1425]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Male 
<typeStatus box="[1005,1107,1399,1425]" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">lectotype</typeStatus>
(Fig. 4) designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Todd EL" box="[390,539,1434,1460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" refId="ref10000" refString="Todd EL (1982) Th e noctuid type material of John B. Smith (Lepidoptera). United States Department of Agriculture, Technical Bulletin 1645, 228 pp." type="book" year="1982">Todd (1982)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<collectionCode box="[549,644,1434,1460]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">AMNH</collectionCode>
; examined. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[779,837,1434,1460]" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Note</emphasis>
– 
<taxonomicName box="[866,1063,1434,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingenua">
<emphasis box="[866,1063,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Charadra ingenua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been a “ghost species,” rarely mentioned in the literature and with few specimens in collections. The 
<typeStatus box="[322,424,1504,1530]" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a specimen typical of eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[779,886,1504,1530]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Colorado</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee, 1852 in Boisduval &amp; Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[892,1014,1504,1531]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphthera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deridens">
<emphasis box="[892,1014,1504,1531]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. deridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
populations, which are slightly smaller and have less contrastingly marked forewings and paler hindwings than eastern North American 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee, 1852 in Boisduval &amp; Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[607,730,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphthera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deridens">
<emphasis box="[607,730,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. deridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of specimens from western 
<collectingRegion box="[235,342,1610,1636]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">Colorado</collectingRegion>
matching the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[601,722,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingenua">
<emphasis box="[601,722,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. ingenua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not distinguishable in genital characters from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee, 1852 in Boisduval &amp; Guenee" authorityYear="1852" box="[323,446,1645,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Diphthera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deridens">
<emphasis box="[323,446,1645,1672]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. deridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so we place 
<taxonomicName box="[596,716,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="176" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingenua" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis box="[596,716,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. ingenua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[725,800,1646,1672]" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in synonymy with 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="15" pageNumber="176">C. deri- dens</emphasis>
. Specimens from the 
<collectingCountry box="[435,559,167,193]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="16" pageNumber="177">Guadalupe</collectingCountry>
Mountains of west Texas reported as 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1107,167,193]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ingenua">
<emphasis box="[987,1107,167,193]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="177">C. ingenua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blanchard A &amp; Franclemont JG" box="[175,575,202,228]" pageId="16" pageNumber="177" pagination="797 - 798" refId="ref9353" refString="Blanchard A, Franclemont JG (1981) Charadra ingenua Smith in west Texas (Lepidoptera: Noctuidae: Pantheinae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 83: 797 - 798" type="journal article" year="1981">Blanchard and Franclemont (1981)</bibRefCitation>
are 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmidt &amp; Anweiler, 2010" authorityName="Schmidt &amp; Anweiler" authorityYear="2010" box="[623,735,202,228]" class="Insecta" family="Pantheidae" genus="Charadra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moneta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[623,735,202,228]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="177">C. moneta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[743,804,202,228]" pageId="16" pageNumber="177" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see below).
</paragraph>
